{
  "stem": "9503.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was slow, and it was convoluted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we finally arrived in Holland, and we were placed in another quarantine-- and I think this one was three weeks-- in the southern part of Holland.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was to make sure that we didn't show up with TB or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we finally were allowed to journey back to Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I do not remember, in any way, the reunion with my uncle.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I only know it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had been hidden during the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But when the Germans had picked us up, and when I had not allowed to be put in the coal bin, he stayed in bed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when the Germans came to our apartment-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and I remember they-- they-- they mowed down flowers that my mother had gotten from-- for-- for her birthday from my father-- my uncle said he can't move.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He's paralyzed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he did have sort of a brace, and he had a cane.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he said there's no way that he can walk.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so they said they would pick him up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then, of course, he took off, and he went underground.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So my uncle survived that way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we stayed first for a while with friends of my parents who had also lived in the same building where we did before the war.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they had escaped to Switzerland, and they had come back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they were very, very caring for us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my mother and I lived with them for a while until my uncle was able to get an apartment, which, oddly enough, was in the same entrance that we lived in before except one story lower, the second floor.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
